The paper proposes a novel deep neural network architecture for unsupervised subspace clustering, which involves non-linear mapping of input data into a latent space and learning pairwise affinities between all data points. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL), which are all relevant to the proposed method.
